<details>
  <summary><b>Response</b></summary>





`HTTP/1.1 201 Created`

E.g.

```json
{
  "id": "6e760b6e-e4f3-42ba-8a2d-afddf44e6cf1"
}
```

Unique identifier of the created Payment Provider. 

</details>

<h3 id="put-payment_providerspayment_provider_id">PUT /payment_providers/{<em>payment_provider_id</em>}</h3>

<p>Update a Payment Provider for a given store. This is especially useful to update the installments specs.</p>

<details>
  <summary><b>Request</b></summary>





[Payment Provider Object](#Properties)

</details>

<details>
  <summary><b>Response</b></summary>





`HTTP/1.1 204 No Content` - the request was successful but there is no representation to return (i.e. the response is empty).

</details>

